Highlights

Performance highlights to date include:

  • $320M - Capital Raised (All Time)

  • $53M - FY23 Capital Raised
  • $5.9M - FY23 Gross Revenue
  • 36% - FY23 Gross Margin
  • $7.6M - FY23 Distributions to investors
  • 74,000 - Registered members
  • $45K - Average investment size
  • 150+ portfolio companies
  • $20M - Unrealised performance fees

Multi-asset Digital Investment Platform

At VentureCrowd, we have developed and created a vertically integrated, full service alternative asset platform and products business that can raise funds from investors for venture and property opportunities, develop complex property projects, provide fund administration and undertake marketing and sales activities. This vertical integration maximises revenue generation from all activities and ensures optimal service delivery to our investors. Our end-to-end digital investment platform offers purpose-driven alternative assets to retail and wholesale investors.

Our product mix includes debt, equity and hybrid securities with differing risk-reward profiles in property and venture capital – previously only available to wholesale investors.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Ventures

VentureCrowd has its origins in venture capital. Founded by a former PwC venture capital partner and one of Australia’s leading venture capital ﬁrms, venture capital began as our core offering. Our venture capital team includes technical specialists who have hands-on experience in venture capital deal structuring, negotiation, transaction documentation, funds administration, portfolio management and compliance.

This deep sector capability has allowed VentureCrowd to be the only such platform in Australia to have delivered 3 succesful venture capital exits. Our team has extensive expertise in securing high quality deal ﬂow, which has resulted in a diverse portfolio of high-growth ventures such as:

Property

VentureCrowd’s property team comprises experienced developers and development managers with the ability to manage end-to-end property development projects internally.

VentureCrowd’s property arm provides proprietary deal flow in a highly attractive alternative asset class and has been an important factor driving revenue, new investor registrations and capital raising volumes.

Our team has the capability to undertake all aspects of the development process, from project origination through to obtaining approvals, managing construction and the sale of off-the-plan dwellings.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Once a development opportunity has been secured, VentureCrowd packages each part of the capital stack for the project separately and offers the opportunity to invest in that financial product to our 72,000+ members. Typically, this includes:

  • Ordinary equity in the initial phase of a project 
  • Preference equity and/or mezzanine debt during the civil construction phase
  • First mortgage loans in the construction phases of a project 


Once a financial product offering is closed, each financial product is managed by our funds management team under the relevant licence. This vertically integrated model is unique to VentureCrowd and allows the business to have complete control over all aspects of the delivery of both the financial product and the underlying asset.

Our Market

As the digitisation of the global investment management sector moves into its most impactful phase yet and the core financial services customer profile shifts from baby boomers to the next generations, technology platforms are replacing legacy investment management organisations and many traditional financial services intermediaries will simply cease to exist.

Impact and purpose-driven investing will continue to rise as millennials and members of Gen Z become the beneficiaries of the largest intergenerational wealth transfer in history and redirect trillions of investment dollars into new, sustainable industries and projects.

Over the next few years, blockchain technology’s practical use cases in the wealthtech sector will achieve mass adoption and by the end of the decade, the transition to Web3 will have profoundly changed the industry.


Market Drivers

VentureCrowd has been at the forefront of the wealth sector’s digital transformation. Looking ahead, the sector is being driven by a number of material macroeconomic trends that are creating strong tailwinds for the business, including:

  • Digitisation and Web3
  • The growing popularity of alternative assets
  • The rise of millennial& Gen Z investors
  • Increasing focus onpurpose-driven investments
  • Lack of trust in traditional financial institutions

While the majority of traditional financial services organisations cautiously observe the impact of these macroeconomic trends, VentureCrowd has built its business in anticipation of them, uniquely positioning the business to advance its position as a leading next-generation digital investment brand.

componentInstanceProperties.value: Growth Strategy

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
VentureCrowd has embarked on its most ambitious growth strategy yet, capitalising on strong historic performance, a highly experienced multi-disciplinary leadership team and advantageous macroeconomic trends to advance its market-leading position into new geographies with a next-generation technology platform.

In addition to continuing to build all aspects of the core Australian business, VentureCrowd’s growth plan involves:

  1. Global expansion into Southeast Asia, the UK & the USA, designed to increase VentureCrowd’s global deal flow, investor base and cross jurisdictional brand awareness.
  2. Web3-based technology platform which includes digitising deal origination (on the front end) enabling higher volumes of qualified deal flow (called Vest Communities), tokenising securities, digitising securities registries (during onboarding), facilitating an ‘always-on’ capital raising capability and providing liquidity via secondary trading (on the back end) which will be used by VentureCrowd itself and licensed to a global market of investment communities, syndicates and future fund managers.

Technology Roadmap

VentureCrowd's existing platform digitises the entire investment process, from deal awareness to portfolio management ...

and we know it works!

Upon completion of the next phase - called VEST - fragmented investment communities all over the world will be able to use our software to manage syndicates and founders will be able to manage their own digital cap table, issue tokens for services, raise bridging finance quickly and easily on their own (we call it always-on capital raising) and offer liquidity for existing shareholders (including themselves and their staff) without the need to list on a stock exchange or be forced into an early sale or merger.

We are positioning VentureCrowd as the only capital partner founders will ever need.

componentInstanceProperties.value: Financial Forecast

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
In FY22 VentureCrowd raised $64,969,300 (110% YoY growth) across 70 projects (148% YoY growth) and generated gross revenue of over $7,742,847 (45% YoY growth), while total distributions to investors exceeded $17,000,000 (95% YoY growth). 

Together with Vest, VentureCrowd is targeting gross revenue of ~$30M in FY25 with gross margins of ~65% (rising to ~86% by FY27) valuing the business at between $255M and $450M (assuming a valuation range between 8.5x and 15x gross revenue) by the end of FY25.

Licensing the Vest Technology to a large and fragmented global market of investment communities, syndicates and future fund managers enables VentureCrowd to expand globally at speed, using industry fragmentation to our advantage rather than as a competitive challenge to be managed.

Business Overview

VentureCrowd has developed a vertically integrated, full service alternative asset platform and products business that can raise funds from investors for venture capital and property opportunities, develop and distribute complex projects, provide fund administration services and undertake marketing and sales activities.

This vertical integration maximises revenue generation from our activities. Our end-to-end digital investment platform offers purpose-driven alternative assets to retail and wholesale investors. Our product mix includes debt, equity and hybrid securities with differing risk-reward profiles in property and venture capital – previously only available to wholesale investors.

Our corporate structure, inclusive of entities facilitating our diverse range of operations, allows us to undertake a breadth of services for ventures, property, and funds opportunities.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The platform has been built, and continues to develop, to adapt and evolve with the changing demands of clients, devices, products and personalisation, and to allow a seamless rollout into Asia (or other foreign markets) in due course.

As a platform, it is low risk, with the customisation around investor experience being predominantly built within the Salesforce environment and the applications based functionality completing the technology stack to provide a secure community.

Leadership

VentureCrowd is driven by a passionate, talented and purpose-driven group of people working hard to find and fund a better future.

Our multidisciplinary expertise enables us to be the only multi-asset digital platform for alternative assets in Australia. Our teams have deep expertise in venture capital, investor relations, funds management, compliance and technology.

Risks

Whilst the directors of VentureCrowd are experienced business managers with deep experience in the key areas that are core to the operation of this business, there are always risks associated with investing in venture capital opportunities which may, either directly or indirectly, result in reduced distributions and/or a loss of some of the capital value of an investment in the Fund. Before deciding whether to subscribe for Units, you should consider whether an investment in this Fund is suitable for you and obtain professional advice.
